ndum etc. || ’éĘ Prepare Price Proposal, Work Order to client for different projects. || Project- HL Bridge over Mahanadi at Pujarapalli Ghat connecting to Jarimuli in || the state of Odisha. || Project- HL Bridge over Mahanadi at Bausuni in the state of Odisha || Project- Repair and Rehabilation of a major bridge at sonapalli in the state of"}]'::jsonb, '[{"title":"Imported accomplishment","description":"ŌŚÅ INSC Young Researcher Award (YRA) from Institute of Scholars at Feb-2023.; ŌŚÅ NPTEL Certificate on ŌĆ£Reinforced Concrete StructuresŌĆØ from IIT Kharagpur.; ŌŚÅ NPTEL Certificate on ŌĆ£Soft Skill Enhancing and PersonalityŌĆØ from IIT Kanpur.; ŌŚÅ Secure 1st in IDEA Competition in JISCE-TECHFEST 2019, Kalyani, West Bengal.; LANGUAGE KNOWN; ŌŚÅ English; ŌŚÅ Bengali; ŌŚÅ Hindi; HOBBIES AND INTERESTS; ŌŚÅ Reading Books; ŌŚÅ Browsing Internet; ŌŚÅ Playing Cricket; ŌŚÅ Travelling; THESIS PAPER/DISSERTATION; Title- Active Vibration Control of a Frame Structure by using Piezoelectric Actuation.; Under Guidance- Prof. Abhishek Hazra & Dr. Goutam Roy; PUBLICATIONS; Evaluated By- Prof.(Dr.) Gokul Mondal, Professor, Jadavpur University, Kolkata-106; ŌŚÅ Active vibration control involves applying force actively in a way that is opposite; and equivalent to the forces that are present due to vibration. Often vibration; causes large displacements to structures which lead to catastrophic failure.; Therefore the research in the control of the large displacements of the structure; due to vibration is an essential part of mechanics. In the present work a plane; frame structure is modeled in ABAQUS CAE to perform linear finite element; analysis (FEA). The mesh convergence study is performed to obtain the suitable; meshing type and the approximate global size. The frame is vibrated by applying a; sinusoidal cyclic load and the maximum displacements in addition to the response; in terms of displacement-time are obtained. At the next step the lateral elements; of the frame are bonded with piezoelectric strips and the piezoelectric strips are; actuated by applying external voltage. The effect of simultaneous application of; voltage on piezoelectric strip and the external sinusoidal dynamic force is; deliberated in terms of the maximum displacement, deformed shape of the frame; and the displacement-time response. The results obtained with and without the; applications of piezoelectric actuation are carefully compared. The comparison; shows a considerable reduction in maximum displacements as well as better; stability of the structure.; ŌŚÅ Impact of COVID-19 in the construction sector and its remedial measures; Presented in IOCER COVID-19 , This research paper was published in the IOP; Science SCOPUS Indexed Journal ŌĆ£ Journal of Physics: Conference seriesŌĆØ.; Feb-2021.; ŌŚÅ Engineered Cementitious Composites: Bendable Concrete; Published in International Journal for Modern Trends in Science and Technology,; ISSN: 2455-3778, VOL- 08, Issue- 05, May-2022, UGC Care.; Published in Journal of Emerging Technology and Innovative Research,; ISSN: 2349-5162, VOL-09, Issue- 05, May-2022, UGC Care."}]'::jsonb, 'F:\Resume All 1\Resume PDF\Ankan CV 3-1-4.pdf', 'Name: Ankan Biswas

